{"id":72331,"date":"2022-01-01T20:19:26","date_gmt":"2022-01-01T19:19:26","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?p=72331"},"modified":"2022-08-12T10:16:25","modified_gmt":"2022-08-12T08:16:25","slug":"uvita","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/costa-rica\/uvita\/","title":{"rendered":"13 Best Things To Do in Uvita, Costa Rica"},"content":{"rendered":"<h2 id=\"todo\">Things to do in Uvita<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"h-1-marino-ballena-whale-tail-great-to-do-in-uvita\">1. Marino Ballena (Whale tail) &#x2013; Great to do in Uvita<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Marino Ballena National Park is a protected reserve located right in the heart of Uvita. During low tide, a natural phenomenon happens where two beaches meet and form a 600-meter wide sand passage in the shape of a whale tail. You&#x2019;re able to walk along the tail during low tide (<a href=\"https:\/\/tideschart.com\/Costa-Rica\/San-Jose\/Perez-Zeledon\/Bahia-Uvita\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">check today&#x2019;s tide here<\/a>). And, as a beautiful coincidence, if you pick the right season, Uvita is the best place for spotting whales &#x2013; more on that later in this travel blog.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/26201947\/uvita-7.jpg\" alt=\"uvita costa rica Marino Ballena National Park\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"304\" alt=\"uvita costa rica Marino Ballena National Park\" class=\"wp-image-72349 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/26201947\/uvita-7.jpg 1920w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/26201947\/uvita-7-800x540.jpg 800w, https:\/\/static.saltinourha