an Jose is to take a direct Tracopa bus or shuttle to Quepos (the town before <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/costa-rica\/manuel-antonio\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Manuel Antonio<\/a>). From Quepos, there are busses every 1-2 hours to Uvita. Alternatively, take a shuttle from Quepos or Manuel Antonio.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--transport \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--transport\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><a href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.12go.asia\/en\/travel\/manuel-antonio\/uvita\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Book your shuttle tickets here.<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"h-getting-around-uvita\">Getting Around Uvita&#xA0;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Although Uvita is a small town it&#x2019;s too large to do everything on foot. To get around town you can rent bikes at <a href=\"https:\/\/goo.gl\/maps\/DNEk1GW6AtbHeWiX6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">La Casa Del Ciclista<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/30163532\/uvita-21-540x810.jpg\" alt=\"uvita costa rica how to get around\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height=\"338\" alt=\"uvita costa rica how to get around\" class=\"wp-image-72548 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/